@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFE0
skinparam noteBorderColor gray

actor "User (Fan/Analyst)" as User
actor "FastF1 Data Source" as DataSrc

rectangle "F1 Insights & Strategy Explorer" {
  usecase "Select Season/Race/Session" as UC1
  usecase "Select Drivers (up to 2)" as UC2
  usecase "View Lap Time Comparison" as UC3
  usecase "View Position Over Laps" as UC4
  usecase "View Tyre Stints" as UC5
}

User --> UC1
User --> UC2
User --> UC3
User --> UC4
User --> UC5

DataSrc --> UC1
DataSrc --> UC3
DataSrc --> UC4
DataSrc --> UC5

UC3 .> UC2 : <<include>>
UC4 .> UC2 : <<include>>
UC5 .> UC2 : <<include>>

note right of User
The User is the primary actor and represents a fan or analyst who interacts with the system to explore Formula 1 race data. The user selects sessions and drivers and views charts to understand performance and strategy in a simple way.
end note

note right of DataSrc
The FastF1 Data Source is a secondary actor representing the external data provider used to retrieve race session data such as lap times, positions, and tyre stints.
end note

note right of UC1
Allows the user to choose the season, race, and session to analyze. This defines the context for all other analysis views.
end note

note right of UC2
Allows the user to select up to two drivers. The selected drivers are used consistently across all visualizations.
end note

note right of UC3
Displays a lap time comparison for the selected drivers to help understand pace differences.
end note

note right of UC4
Shows how driver positions change over laps, highlighting overtakes and position changes.
end note

note right of UC5
Displays tyre stint information including compounds and pit-stop timing to explain strategy choices.
end note
@enduml
